WEBVTT

00:01.697 --> 00:02.828
[whoosh]

00:03.786 --> 00:05.875
[fire crackling]

00:10.140 --> 00:14.231
[thunderstorm]

00:19.758 --> 00:23.632
[booming]

00:28.985 --> 00:32.293
♪

00:32.336 --> 00:34.643
[glass shattering]

00:45.523 --> 00:50.398
[ominous music ♪]

01:08.111 --> 01:10.853
[computer keys clacking]

01:17.468 --> 01:18.426
[speaks Russian]

01:18.469 --> 01:19.514
My name is Rosa,

01:19.557 --> 01:21.603
and I'm 25 years old.

01:21.646 --> 01:23.953
I would like
to find generous man

01:23.996 --> 01:25.955
to be my future husband.

01:25.998 --> 01:26.912
I do believe--

01:26.956 --> 01:28.262
...American man

01:28.305 --> 01:31.134
who will be kind, sharing,
and loves to travel.

01:31.178 --> 01:32.179
Since I was a child--

01:32.222 --> 01:33.267
[speaks Russian]

01:33.310 --> 01:35.095
I am Elena,
environmental engineer--

01:35.138 --> 01:38.098
- I enjoy moonlight walks--
- I will be a good wife--

01:38.141 --> 01:42.102
- ...and I'm looking forward
to meet a husband--
- ...and intelligent man

01:42.145 --> 01:44.669
to create a family.

01:46.106 --> 01:47.629
[Nina, on computer]
Hello.

01:49.109 --> 01:52.634
My name is Nina,
and I'm from Livny.

01:52.677 --> 01:54.375
I'm a good cook.

01:54.418 --> 01:57.639
Some say that food is the
key to man's heart, so,

01:57.682 --> 01:58.727
I hope so.

01:58.770 --> 02:02.034
I like lilies.
I like to grow them.

02:02.078 --> 02:05.647
Having roots is important
for me, so...

02:05.690 --> 02:07.388
Come here and say hi.

02:07.431 --> 02:09.868
[gentle music ♪]

02:09.912 --> 02:12.349
This is Dasha,
my daughter.

02:12.393 --> 02:14.046
She is my sunshine.

02:14.090 --> 02:16.179
So, I hope you're out there

02:16.223 --> 02:19.182
watching us now, and...
like what you see.

02:19.226 --> 02:21.793
[audio rewinding]
...like what you see.

02:21.837 --> 02:26.058
[dramatic music ♪]

02:34.937 --> 02:38.070
[electricity buzzing]

02:40.160 --> 02:43.075
[dramatic whoosh]

02:45.252 --> 02:49.081
[unsettling music ♪]

02:56.567 --> 02:57.742
Nina!

02:59.266 --> 03:02.138
[speaking Russian]

04:01.110 --> 04:03.330
[dog barking]

04:03.373 --> 04:06.768
[dramatic music ♪]

04:09.814 --> 04:13.253
[somber music ♪]

04:56.383 --> 04:58.863
[pipes shudder loudly]

05:14.488 --> 05:15.358
[siren wailing]

05:15.402 --> 05:17.839
[Woman speaking Russian]

05:51.655 --> 05:54.092
[car horn honking]

05:54.136 --> 05:55.442
[gentle music ♪]

06:20.945 --> 06:23.731
[jet engine roaring]

06:23.774 --> 06:27.299
[dramatic music ♪]

06:49.539 --> 06:51.541
[speaking Russian]

07:27.142 --> 07:30.406
[indistinct PA announcement]

07:30.450 --> 07:33.496
♪

07:46.378 --> 07:48.076
Karl.

07:48.119 --> 07:50.295
Oh, my God.

07:50.339 --> 07:53.821
I'm sorry, customs took
so long, so many questions.

07:53.864 --> 07:56.519
[Karl]
Quite all right.
You're here.

07:56.563 --> 07:58.042
That's all that matters.

07:59.479 --> 08:01.437
You're even more beautiful
in person.

08:02.569 --> 08:03.308
Thank you.

08:04.527 --> 08:06.790
Lilies, you remembered, oh!
- Yes, yes.

08:08.183 --> 08:10.359
[speaks Russian], Dasha.

08:10.402 --> 08:13.971
Thank you to welcome us
to America.

08:14.015 --> 08:21.979
[speaking broken Russian]

08:23.415 --> 08:27.289
[pensive, dramatic music ♪]

08:48.571 --> 08:50.573
I can't believe
you're really here.

08:50.617 --> 08:52.488
Me too.

08:52.532 --> 08:56.579
It could take weeks,
maybe months, to believe
this is really happening.

08:58.625 --> 09:00.496
Do you always travel
by driver?

09:00.540 --> 09:01.932
Hagen isn't only a driver,

09:01.976 --> 09:03.978
he takes care of everything
around the estate.

09:04.021 --> 09:06.371
My father adopted him
from an orphanage in Hungary.

09:08.286 --> 09:11.202
Don't expect
too much conversation,

09:11.246 --> 09:13.248
he was born without a tongue.

09:13.291 --> 09:16.860
♪

09:18.819 --> 09:20.429
That's you new home, Dasha.

09:20.472 --> 09:24.085
Home? That's castle.

09:24.128 --> 09:28.480
♪

09:47.499 --> 09:48.805
[music fades]

09:48.849 --> 09:51.025
When I was a boy,
this place was full of life.

09:51.068 --> 09:56.117
My father used
to throw lavish ballroom parties
and masquerades.

09:56.160 --> 09:59.294
There was always
something going on.

09:59.337 --> 10:00.904
It's so beautiful.

10:00.948 --> 10:02.689
The house is fully stocked
during the winters,

10:02.732 --> 10:05.256
so you'll never need to
leave the grounds.

10:05.300 --> 10:06.910
We are far from prying eyes.

10:06.954 --> 10:09.913
The closest neighbor
is 20 miles away.

10:14.744 --> 10:16.572
Do you ever get lonely?

10:17.442 --> 10:18.574
Not anymore.

10:22.099 --> 10:24.145
- She's asking if Hagen
lives with us.
- No.

10:24.188 --> 10:26.277
No, no, Hagen lives
in the barn.

10:26.321 --> 10:27.844
Just down the road.

10:27.888 --> 10:29.106
By his own choice.

10:29.150 --> 10:31.543
I think he likes
to be alone.

10:41.945 --> 10:42.903
[clock chimes]

10:42.946 --> 10:44.513
Ladies,

10:44.556 --> 10:46.428
this is Maria.

10:46.471 --> 10:48.082
It's a pleasure to meet you.

10:48.125 --> 10:49.649
Hello.

10:49.692 --> 10:52.564
Oh, this must be Dasha.

10:52.608 --> 10:54.654
So very lovely.

10:55.567 --> 10:58.527
Like a little angel
sent from heaven.

10:58.570 --> 11:00.268
[Karl]
Maria never had
children of her own,

11:00.311 --> 11:02.574
so she's been looking forward
to this.

11:03.663 --> 11:04.925
Say hello to Maria.

11:04.968 --> 11:06.709
[yawning]
Hello.

11:06.753 --> 11:08.406
[Nina]
I'm sorry, it's been
a long flight.

11:08.450 --> 11:09.625
she is so tired.

11:09.669 --> 11:10.887
Perfectly understandable.

11:10.931 --> 11:12.628
So why don't we go upstairs,
freshen up,

11:12.672 --> 11:14.412
and have a little rest
before dinner?

11:14.456 --> 11:15.805
It's a good idea.

11:15.849 --> 11:17.459
Is this everything?

11:17.502 --> 11:18.721
You said
not to bring much, so...

11:18.765 --> 11:20.592
I did.

11:20.636 --> 11:23.726
Because I had Maria go out
and get you each
a brand new wardrobe.

11:23.770 --> 11:25.162
That's so kind of you.

11:25.206 --> 11:26.555
[Karl]
This way.

11:26.598 --> 11:28.122
[Nina]
How did you know
our sizes?

11:28.165 --> 11:30.385
Oh, I took look
at your physical exams.

11:30.428 --> 11:32.517
I wanted to surprise you.

11:37.784 --> 11:40.308
Wow. So many doors.

11:40.351 --> 11:42.310
What is behind this one?

11:42.353 --> 11:44.616
Oh, that's Maria's
side of the house.

11:44.660 --> 11:48.098
It's off limits.
She likes her privacy.

11:48.142 --> 11:50.013
But, this door...

11:51.188 --> 11:53.190
...is of great significance.

11:54.104 --> 11:56.759
This is where
the princess sleeps.

11:56.803 --> 12:01.068
[gentle music ♪]

12:01.111 --> 12:03.635
Karl, it's amazing.

12:03.679 --> 12:04.811
[gasps]

12:04.854 --> 12:06.943
Dashinka, what do you say?

12:06.987 --> 12:08.379
Thank you.

12:08.815 --> 12:09.903
I'll tell you what.

12:09.946 --> 12:12.383
Why don't you settle in,
get comfortable.

12:12.427 --> 12:14.734
I'm gonna show your mom
the master bedroom.

12:16.692 --> 12:20.130
And we...
have an elevator.

12:20.174 --> 12:22.829
It's the only other access
to the second floor.

12:22.872 --> 12:24.700
[grunts]

12:24.744 --> 12:26.963
I prefer to take the stairs.

12:27.007 --> 12:30.227
She's old and has
a mind of her own.

12:30.271 --> 12:33.448
[Dasha humming softly]

12:41.630 --> 12:43.588
[speaking Russian]

12:58.299 --> 13:00.431
[Nina]
Funny how life is.

13:00.475 --> 13:03.739
One day you're struggling
to feed your child...

13:03.783 --> 13:07.177
...and the next you have
servants at your feet.

13:07.221 --> 13:08.744
Mom?

13:10.354 --> 13:13.836
[Nina]
I-I really wish you had come
visit us in Russia.

13:13.880 --> 13:15.969
Oh, Nina...

13:16.012 --> 13:17.840
You know I don't fly.

13:17.884 --> 13:21.844
The idea of putting my life
into somebody else's hands...

13:21.888 --> 13:23.498
...terrifies me.

13:25.630 --> 13:26.806
Mom?

13:29.809 --> 13:31.288
Are you having doubts?

13:31.332 --> 13:33.247
Oh, no, no... It's just...

13:33.290 --> 13:36.728
my mother and sister, they
worry about me and Dasha.

13:36.772 --> 13:40.341
♪

13:40.820 --> 13:42.952
Which reminds me...

13:42.996 --> 13:46.347
It's yours for whenever you
feel the need to call home.

13:46.390 --> 13:48.740
[speaks Russian]

13:55.922 --> 13:57.401
[speaking Russian]

13:59.099 --> 14:01.188
Thank you, Karl.

14:01.231 --> 14:03.320
It means so much.

14:03.364 --> 14:04.844
[door creaks]

14:04.887 --> 14:06.410
[deep growling]

14:06.454 --> 14:08.848
[dramatic musical sting ♪]

14:08.891 --> 14:10.632
[panting]

14:13.635 --> 14:15.985
[eerie music ♪]

14:29.999 --> 14:31.305
[screams]

14:31.348 --> 14:32.784
- Dasha?
- Reign?!

14:32.828 --> 14:34.351
[barking]

14:34.395 --> 14:35.831
Reign!

14:37.833 --> 14:39.922
No!
- Dasha?

14:39.966 --> 14:42.185
Are you okay?
Did the dog hurt you?

14:42.229 --> 14:43.578
He'd never hurt her.
He's well trained.

14:43.621 --> 14:44.927
He only attacks on command.

14:44.971 --> 14:46.842
I saw a woman in the closet.

14:46.886 --> 14:48.844
A woman in the closet?

14:52.979 --> 14:54.197
It's just a mannequin.

14:54.241 --> 14:55.416
[Karl]
It's my ex-wife's
wedding dress.

14:55.459 --> 14:56.896
She liked to keep it.

14:56.939 --> 14:58.854
I-I just put it away.

14:58.898 --> 15:00.464
What is this room?

15:00.508 --> 15:01.813
My son's.

15:01.857 --> 15:02.902
Your son?

15:02.945 --> 15:04.468
You never mentioned a son.

15:05.861 --> 15:08.429
I didn't mention it, because I
wasn't ready to talk about it.

15:09.909 --> 15:13.347
He was born
with mitochondrial disease.

15:13.390 --> 15:16.176
By the time we realized
something was wrong,

15:16.219 --> 15:19.875
many of the organs in his body
were already destroyed.

15:19.919 --> 15:23.879
I cannot imagine how you
and your wife suffered.

15:23.923 --> 15:26.490
Took a toll on both of us.

15:26.534 --> 15:28.840
Eventually, we grew apart and...

15:28.884 --> 15:31.060
...she left...

15:31.104 --> 15:33.062
Never even said goodbye.

15:33.845 --> 15:35.369
I'm sorry.

15:35.412 --> 15:38.328
[fire crackling]

15:41.070 --> 15:42.506
[Karl]
Dasha.

15:43.290 --> 15:45.466
Did you enjoy Maria's cooking?

15:47.424 --> 15:49.078
Russian food
is very different.

15:50.471 --> 15:53.996
One of these days,
I have to cook you
a nice Russian meal.

15:54.040 --> 15:56.085
[boom]

15:56.129 --> 16:00.437
[eerie ambience]

16:00.481 --> 16:02.570
[sighs]
I forgot to mention,

16:02.613 --> 16:05.181
that we
have frequent power outages.

16:05.225 --> 16:06.878
That noise you hear

16:06.922 --> 16:09.925
is a backup generator.
It's very old.

16:11.100 --> 16:13.276
Sometimes the house shakes.

16:13.320 --> 16:15.887
[ominous shuddering]

16:15.931 --> 16:19.674
[dramatic music ♪]

16:27.029 --> 16:28.509
[crickets chirping]

16:28.552 --> 16:32.339
[speaking Russian]

16:49.182 --> 16:51.488
I think house is too big.

16:51.532 --> 16:53.055
It scares me.

16:53.099 --> 16:56.580
Well, you always liked
a good adventure.

16:56.624 --> 16:58.017
And it's haunted.

16:58.060 --> 17:00.193
Dashinka, it was
just a mannequin.

17:00.236 --> 17:01.107
You saw it yourself.

17:01.150 --> 17:02.804
But I heard her breathing.

17:02.847 --> 17:04.501
No. [speaks Russian]

17:08.331 --> 17:10.986
[gentle music ♪]

17:20.735 --> 17:24.913
[Nina speaking Russian]

17:44.846 --> 17:46.326
That was my mother.

17:46.369 --> 17:47.979
It's morning in Russia.

17:48.023 --> 17:50.025
Oh, that's right.

17:50.069 --> 17:53.072
Sometimes I forget
the world isn't flat.

17:57.989 --> 17:59.513
Do you like the house?

17:59.556 --> 18:01.602
Yes, of course.

18:01.645 --> 18:03.038
Who wouldn't?

18:08.565 --> 18:10.959
After our many
late-night rendezvous...

18:12.178 --> 18:15.877
I thought I painted
the perfect picture of you.

18:18.053 --> 18:20.403
But you're nothing
like I imagined.

18:22.188 --> 18:25.321
I'm sorry,
it's been a long day,
I'm must look so bad.

18:25.365 --> 18:26.583
Quite the contrary.

18:27.758 --> 18:31.719
The only word that comes
to mind is "Aphrodite."

19:03.272 --> 19:09.060
[pensive classical music ♪]

19:09.104 --> 19:14.109
[Karl gasping sexually]

19:29.168 --> 19:31.474
[Priest]
You may now kiss the bride.

19:31.518 --> 19:34.085
[crowd applauding]

19:41.919 --> 19:43.704
[applause dies down]

19:43.747 --> 19:46.054
Ah, thank you, Maria.

19:47.838 --> 19:49.666
I'd like you to meet
some friends.

19:49.710 --> 19:51.755
First off,
this is John Buchanan.

19:51.799 --> 19:53.235
He's an old family friend.

19:53.279 --> 19:54.932
Hello. Thank you for coming.

19:54.976 --> 19:58.109
The pleasure is all mine.

19:58.153 --> 19:59.154
[Nina giggles]

19:59.198 --> 20:01.112
Yes, thank you, John.

20:01.896 --> 20:04.246
It's amazing
what money can buy.

20:04.290 --> 20:06.161
This is my cousin Claire.

20:06.205 --> 20:09.338
She is the Iron Lady
of the family.

20:09.382 --> 20:12.254
Congratulations, dear.

20:12.298 --> 20:14.387
And her son, Keller.
He's a fine young man.

20:14.430 --> 20:19.261
He's in med school.
He is going to be
a brilliant surgeon one day.

20:19.305 --> 20:22.264
Better be.
I'm paying for his education.

20:22.308 --> 20:23.265
Just remember, darling.

20:23.309 --> 20:24.875
The key
to a successful marriage

20:24.919 --> 20:27.313
is knowing how to keep
to other happy.

20:27.356 --> 20:29.271
Just not too happy.

20:29.315 --> 20:30.620
[both laugh]

20:30.664 --> 20:33.232
Just wait 'til I make him
real Russian dinner.

20:33.275 --> 20:36.365
He will eat from my hand
like Reign.

20:36.409 --> 20:40.195
[traditional violin music ♪]

20:53.164 --> 20:57.778
[crowd clapping in rhythm]

21:13.315 --> 21:14.403
[song ends]

21:14.447 --> 21:16.318
[tapping on glass]

21:16.362 --> 21:18.189
[Russian accent]
I'd like to make toast

21:18.233 --> 21:20.453
to my friend, Karl Frederick,

21:20.496 --> 21:22.498
and his new bride,

21:22.542 --> 21:25.632
and her lovely daughter,
Dasha.

21:25.675 --> 21:28.330
It's been over a year

21:28.374 --> 21:32.029
since Karl was faced
with terrible tragedy

21:32.073 --> 21:35.032
and I must admit
I was worried.

21:35.076 --> 21:36.643
But I assured him

21:36.686 --> 21:38.384
it was not the end,

21:38.427 --> 21:40.951
that there were others
out there...

21:40.995 --> 21:45.304
other fishes in the sea,
with children...

21:45.347 --> 21:47.349
like Tyler.

21:47.393 --> 21:48.307
So...

21:48.350 --> 21:50.352
we were there
for you then,

21:50.396 --> 21:53.268
we are here for you now...

21:53.312 --> 21:57.664
and now Dasha
and Nina are here, too.

21:57.707 --> 21:59.361
To new beginnings.

21:59.405 --> 22:01.581
[all]
To new beginnings.

22:01.624 --> 22:03.844
[glasses clinking]

22:03.887 --> 22:06.020
[Yuri, Russian accent]
When communism fell

22:06.063 --> 22:07.717
it was like Wild West.

22:07.761 --> 22:10.329
Uneducated hoodlums
with the biggest balls

22:10.372 --> 22:11.852
took control of everything,

22:11.895 --> 22:14.333
factories, oil, gas.

22:14.376 --> 22:16.857
They became powerful overnight.

22:16.900 --> 22:19.250
I'm sorry.
I don't remember meeting you.

22:19.294 --> 22:20.556
I'm sorry.

22:20.600 --> 22:21.992
This is Cranston.

22:22.036 --> 22:23.690
He's a longtime family friend.

22:23.733 --> 22:26.388
For years, he helped me
run the clinic
here in the house.

22:26.432 --> 22:28.651
I read somewhere
about your clinic.

22:28.695 --> 22:30.827
Didn't health inspectors
shut it down

22:30.871 --> 22:32.612
after a young girl died?

22:32.655 --> 22:34.831
A young girl died...

22:34.875 --> 22:36.006
[ominous music ♪]

22:36.050 --> 22:36.616
...here?

22:36.659 --> 22:38.400
But first, okay.

22:38.444 --> 22:39.706
Let's get the record straight.

22:39.749 --> 22:41.403
She was of legal age.

22:41.447 --> 22:44.450
Here on an extended stay
after a breast augmentation.

22:44.493 --> 22:46.669
She kept demanding
something for the pain,

22:46.713 --> 22:49.324
so I gave her diamorphine.

22:49.368 --> 22:51.282
Little did I know,

22:51.326 --> 22:53.241
she brought cocaine
to the party.

22:53.284 --> 22:56.244
Morphine is a depressant.

22:56.287 --> 22:58.333
Cocaine is a stimulant.

22:58.377 --> 23:00.422
One slows down the heart,

23:00.466 --> 23:02.859
the other speeds it up.

23:02.903 --> 23:05.775
Yeah,
it's called speed-ballin'.

23:09.083 --> 23:11.215
Sounds like you've been
doing some digging, Yuri.

23:11.259 --> 23:13.522
When I hear my niece
is leaving everything behind

23:13.566 --> 23:15.350
for a man she hardly knows,

23:15.394 --> 23:17.134
I must put my nose
in the dirt.

23:17.178 --> 23:19.615
- Yuri.
- [Karl] It's quite all right.

23:19.659 --> 23:21.400
None of it's a secret.

23:22.488 --> 23:23.924
It's just not relevant.

23:23.967 --> 23:25.491
♪

23:25.534 --> 23:28.537
Well, it's getting late.

23:28.581 --> 23:30.060
I should be going.

23:30.104 --> 23:31.410
Are you okay to drive?

23:31.453 --> 23:32.889
[Karl]
He'll be fine.

23:32.933 --> 23:35.892
Vodka's like water
to the Russian blood.

23:35.936 --> 23:36.893
Isn't that right, Yuri?

23:36.937 --> 23:38.634
That's right.

23:38.678 --> 23:40.810
And now that we live
so close...

23:40.854 --> 23:42.377
I'll be sure to visit...

23:43.726 --> 23:44.814
...often.

23:45.511 --> 23:46.947
Please do.

23:48.470 --> 23:50.951
[wind blowing]

23:50.994 --> 23:53.170
[speaking Russian]

24:10.797 --> 24:13.408
♪

24:13.452 --> 24:15.410
[engine starts]

24:20.459 --> 24:23.505
[wind howling outside]

24:38.825 --> 24:40.391
[door creaks open, shuts]

24:43.220 --> 24:44.308
Karl?

24:45.919 --> 24:47.224
[snorting]

24:47.268 --> 24:48.399
[gasps]

24:49.618 --> 24:51.359
I'm sorry.

24:51.402 --> 24:52.534
I should have knocked.

24:52.578 --> 24:54.754
No, don't be silly.

24:54.797 --> 24:57.278
Mi casa es su casa.

24:57.321 --> 24:59.367
[chilling music ♪]

24:59.410 --> 25:00.847
Would you like some?

25:03.502 --> 25:04.851
I had no idea.

25:05.460 --> 25:06.635
Nina,

25:06.679 --> 25:09.551
I'm 63 years old.

25:09.595 --> 25:12.206
I've survived
the rollercoaster of life.

25:12.249 --> 25:13.816
I've had heartache
and tragedy

25:13.860 --> 25:15.557
like no one else.

25:15.601 --> 25:18.038
I think I've earned
my vices.

25:19.213 --> 25:22.738
I swear to Dasha
everything would be different.

25:22.782 --> 25:24.740
I thought you were different.

25:24.784 --> 25:26.525
What are you talking about?

25:28.178 --> 25:30.572
Just don't ever do it
around Dasha.

25:30.616 --> 25:33.053
♪

25:36.578 --> 25:39.407
[dramatic music ♪]

25:39.450 --> 25:41.627
[wind howling]

25:41.670 --> 25:46.022
[rock music in Russian
on radio ♪]

26:07.087 --> 26:08.218
[Yuri cries out]

26:08.262 --> 26:10.003
[crash]

26:10.046 --> 26:12.919
[chilling music ♪]

26:23.016 --> 26:27.629
[rock music continues ♪]

26:38.509 --> 26:40.163
What are you doing?!

26:41.295 --> 26:42.644
What are you doing?!

26:42.688 --> 26:45.473
[chilling music ♪]

26:46.692 --> 26:47.649
No!

26:47.693 --> 26:49.651
No! No!

26:49.695 --> 26:53.089
No!
[screams]

26:59.530 --> 27:01.271
[both laughing]

27:01.315 --> 27:05.711
[luxurious, dramatic music ♪]

27:08.583 --> 27:10.672
[speaks Russian]

27:10.716 --> 27:13.980
[both laugh]

27:26.209 --> 27:28.777
[speaking Russian]

28:03.682 --> 28:06.467
[hammer clanking]

28:10.732 --> 28:11.690
There.

28:11.733 --> 28:13.082
Just like new.

28:17.870 --> 28:20.176
[Maria curses in Spanish]

28:20.786 --> 28:22.788
[Dasha]
Hola, Maria!

28:22.831 --> 28:25.399
Hagen, Hagen,
I need your help!

28:25.442 --> 28:27.183
Maria, are you okay?

28:27.227 --> 28:29.316
I lowered the lamp
to dust it,

28:29.359 --> 28:31.492
but now it won't go back up.

28:31.535 --> 28:33.494
Maybe I can help.

28:33.537 --> 28:35.670
My father was a mechanic
on a ship,

28:35.714 --> 28:38.107
and I watch him work winches
like this.

28:39.979 --> 28:41.632
Pull on the chain.

28:42.546 --> 28:43.591
Harder.

28:43.634 --> 28:45.898
My father was very handy.

28:45.941 --> 28:48.988
He used to say
if he was stranded
on the island,

28:49.031 --> 28:50.990
all he need is a hammer
to survive.

28:56.386 --> 28:59.694
[dramatic music ♪]

28:59.738 --> 29:03.654
[gears, chains clattering]

29:09.138 --> 29:10.139
There.

29:10.183 --> 29:11.837
The braking mechanism
was stuck.

29:11.880 --> 29:13.534
Maybe it needs oil.

29:13.577 --> 29:14.753
[gentle music ♪]

29:14.796 --> 29:16.755
Maria, can I
ask you something?

29:16.798 --> 29:17.756
Of course.

29:18.887 --> 29:20.802
Last night, I walked in
on Karl doing--

29:20.846 --> 29:22.499
Cocaina.

29:23.326 --> 29:24.806
Yes, um...

29:24.850 --> 29:27.809
It started
when Tyler became ill.

29:27.853 --> 29:30.899
The drugs helped him
to cope with the pain.

29:33.336 --> 29:34.860
Thank you for sharing that.

29:34.903 --> 29:37.950
♪

29:42.258 --> 29:43.433
[Karl]
The situation?

29:43.477 --> 29:45.827
The situation is
getting worse by the day.

29:45.871 --> 29:47.307
Not to mention all the snow
we're having.

29:47.350 --> 29:48.874
It's not gonna be easy
getting up here.

29:50.876 --> 29:52.138
Not my problem!

29:52.878 --> 29:55.576
Already paid him
a lot of money.

29:55.619 --> 29:57.970
Just get him up here.

29:58.013 --> 29:59.841
You better be
as good as you say.

30:03.932 --> 30:05.847
Is everything okay?

30:05.891 --> 30:07.849
Yeah. My cousin, Claire,

30:07.893 --> 30:10.286
she has a friend who's
an expert in old homes.

30:10.330 --> 30:13.768
I'm trying to get him up here
to fix the power situation.

30:13.812 --> 30:16.205
In worst case,
we can use candles.

30:16.249 --> 30:18.425
Can be very romantic.

30:18.468 --> 30:23.865
[dramatic classical
piano music ♪]

30:23.909 --> 30:26.607
[cutlery clinking]

30:30.959 --> 30:34.267
[Dasha coughing]

30:34.310 --> 30:37.357
Dashinka, are you catching
a cold?

30:37.400 --> 30:39.054
It's a fever.

30:39.098 --> 30:41.230
That's a shame.

30:41.274 --> 30:45.365
I was really hoping
the three of us could
go horseback riding tomorrow.

30:45.408 --> 30:47.106
What a wonderful idea.

30:47.149 --> 30:48.890
You two should still go.

30:48.934 --> 30:50.500
I can watch Dasha.

30:50.544 --> 30:54.156
Newlyweds should spend time
alone, no?

30:55.636 --> 30:58.204
Sure. That sounds
like a great idea.

30:58.247 --> 31:01.207
♪

31:04.819 --> 31:07.866
[wind howling]

31:07.909 --> 31:10.303
[eerie music ♪]

31:10.346 --> 31:11.695
[Karl]
Stop it.

31:20.574 --> 31:22.881
Not now.
Please, not now.

31:25.535 --> 31:27.842
I said stop it!

31:30.018 --> 31:31.933
Damn it!
It's not your decision!

31:31.977 --> 31:33.195
[dramatic music sting ♪]

31:33.239 --> 31:35.328
[on TV]
She's done it.
The perfect crime.

31:35.371 --> 31:36.938
Has she killed him?

31:36.982 --> 31:38.548
Not yet.

31:38.592 --> 31:39.767
But she will.

31:39.810 --> 31:44.598
[ominous, pensive music ♪]

31:44.641 --> 31:45.816
[Woman on TV]
David?

31:45.860 --> 31:50.952
[on TV, door creaks, slams]

31:55.000 --> 31:57.524
Drink this tea.

31:58.525 --> 31:59.961
Every drop.

32:00.005 --> 32:02.833
♪

32:17.022 --> 32:23.245
♪

32:27.032 --> 32:28.816
It's coming back to me, Karl.

32:28.859 --> 32:30.861
It's like riding a bike.

32:33.038 --> 32:34.996
[Man on TV
speaks indistinctly]

32:35.040 --> 32:37.172
[Man on TV]
...even my life.

32:37.216 --> 32:40.262
But you're not going
to live to enjoy it.

32:43.048 --> 32:45.093
It's so beautiful, Karl.

32:47.008 --> 32:52.622
[Woman on TV screaming]

32:52.666 --> 32:54.537
[dramatic musical sting ♪]

32:57.888 --> 32:59.803
[eerie music ♪]

32:59.847 --> 33:02.763
[electricity buzzing,
generator clunking]

33:09.988 --> 33:12.991
[door creaks]

33:20.607 --> 33:24.002
[dramatic, ominous music ♪]

33:28.832 --> 33:29.964
Maria?

33:30.008 --> 33:33.011
[electricity hums]

33:37.276 --> 33:39.974
[ghostly whispers]

33:44.109 --> 33:47.938
All right, Nina.
How 'bout you show me
what you got?

33:47.982 --> 33:50.941
[dramatic musical sting ♪]

33:50.985 --> 33:52.943
[chilling shout]

33:55.816 --> 33:57.296
[growl]

33:57.339 --> 33:59.211
Mama!

34:00.125 --> 34:02.518
[Karl]
C'mon, Nina!

34:02.562 --> 34:04.085
[Nina cries out]

34:04.129 --> 34:07.871
[dramatic, tense music ♪]

34:14.139 --> 34:15.053
[Nina]
Please!

34:15.096 --> 34:17.707
[speaks indistinctly]

34:17.751 --> 34:19.666
[Karl whoops]

34:19.709 --> 34:22.538
♪

34:22.582 --> 34:24.932
[hooves thumping]

34:24.975 --> 34:27.065
[leather creaking]

34:29.937 --> 34:31.243
Slow down!

34:31.286 --> 34:33.071
[crying out]

34:37.814 --> 34:39.599
Whoa, whoa.
[horse grunts]

34:40.774 --> 34:42.384
[horse snorts]

34:42.428 --> 34:43.733
Nina?!

34:43.777 --> 34:46.258
[wind howling]

34:46.301 --> 34:48.782
[crow cawing]

34:54.831 --> 34:56.224
Nina?!

34:59.271 --> 35:02.100
[Karl gasping]

35:02.143 --> 35:04.798
[dramatic music ♪]

35:06.887 --> 35:07.931
Nina...

35:13.023 --> 35:15.722
[panting]

35:20.509 --> 35:24.122
[breathing heavily]

35:26.036 --> 35:28.082
[grunts]

35:28.126 --> 35:31.129
[panting]

35:36.046 --> 35:38.223
♪

35:38.266 --> 35:39.398
Dasha?!

35:40.181 --> 35:43.010
Dasha?!
Dasha, no!

35:43.053 --> 35:45.360
[crack]

35:45.404 --> 35:47.014
♪

35:47.057 --> 35:48.798
Dasha!

35:48.842 --> 35:51.018
[water bubbling]

35:52.106 --> 35:53.194
Dasha!

35:53.238 --> 35:55.109
[panting]

35:56.154 --> 35:59.896
♪

35:59.940 --> 36:01.202
Dasha!

36:01.246 --> 36:03.422
Dasha! Oh! Come, come!

36:03.465 --> 36:06.207
[groaning]
Oh!

36:06.251 --> 36:08.905
[grunting]

36:11.256 --> 36:13.649
[groaning]

36:13.693 --> 36:15.085
Oh! Oh, Dasha.

36:15.129 --> 36:16.565
Dasha, come on, baby.

36:16.609 --> 36:18.219
Come on, Dasha!

36:18.263 --> 36:19.481
Come on! Ugh!

36:19.525 --> 36:22.223
[grunting]

36:24.921 --> 36:26.445
Dasha?

36:26.488 --> 36:28.316
Dasha?!

36:28.360 --> 36:30.231
[grunting]

36:30.275 --> 36:31.711
Dasha!

36:32.277 --> 36:34.104
Dasha!

36:34.148 --> 36:37.238
[grunting]
You can't do this.
We're so close!

36:37.282 --> 36:39.240
Not after everything!

36:39.284 --> 36:42.287
[Dasha coughing]
[Karl gasping]

36:42.330 --> 36:44.506
Oh, thank God!
Oh, God!

36:44.550 --> 36:46.116
My daughter!

36:46.160 --> 36:48.118
No, no, no!

36:48.162 --> 36:52.079
[both crying, gasping]

36:52.122 --> 36:54.429
[eerie ambience]

36:54.473 --> 36:56.170
[Nina]
Maybe we should take her
to the hospital.

36:56.214 --> 36:58.085
[Maria]
The snow makes the roads
impassable.

36:58.128 --> 36:59.260
The best thing to do right now

36:59.304 --> 37:00.957
is to get her out of these
wet clothes

37:01.001 --> 37:03.221
and into a warm bed.

37:04.396 --> 37:06.615
We have plenty
of medical supplies left over

37:06.659 --> 37:09.531
from Mr. Frederick's clinic
if we need it.

37:13.927 --> 37:19.019
[unsettling nursery music ♪]

37:19.759 --> 37:21.717
What happened to you?

37:21.761 --> 37:23.937
[gentle music ♪]

37:23.980 --> 37:25.895
It's nothing.

37:25.939 --> 37:28.768
Silly me.
I fell from the horse.

37:30.857 --> 37:33.120
But you, Dashinka,

37:33.163 --> 37:36.210
why were you so far away
from the house?

37:36.254 --> 37:37.820
To look for you.

37:37.864 --> 37:41.259
But you knew I was going
for the ride with Karl.

37:41.302 --> 37:43.435
You knew I was coming back.

37:45.350 --> 37:46.655
I saw a ghost.

37:46.699 --> 37:49.484
[eerie music ♪]

37:49.528 --> 37:52.182
- A ghost?
- A lady ghost.

37:52.226 --> 37:54.663
Dashinka, there is
no such things as ghosts.

37:54.707 --> 37:58.319
She said he is going
to do bad things to us.

37:58.363 --> 37:59.364
Who?

37:59.407 --> 38:01.540
Karl! She said
if we don't leave

38:01.583 --> 38:02.758
he'll kill us both!

38:02.802 --> 38:05.326
Dasha, stop it!

38:05.370 --> 38:06.719
That's enough.

38:06.762 --> 38:09.243
♪

38:10.375 --> 38:11.985
I'm sorry, sweetheart.

38:16.816 --> 38:20.123
[ominous music ♪]

38:31.874 --> 38:33.223
[snorting]

38:33.267 --> 38:35.095
Why, Karl?

38:36.662 --> 38:38.228
'Cause I do.

38:38.272 --> 38:39.273
I just do.

38:41.231 --> 38:43.233
[snorting]

38:43.277 --> 38:45.192
Karl, I'm grateful

38:45.235 --> 38:46.411
you saved Dasha's life.

38:46.454 --> 38:48.978
What was she doing out there
anyway, huh?

38:49.022 --> 38:50.240
I don't know.

38:50.284 --> 38:52.547
She says she got scared.

38:52.591 --> 38:54.854
She says she saw a ghost.

38:56.595 --> 38:58.379
A ghost?

38:58.423 --> 38:59.815
Yes.

39:01.251 --> 39:02.775
What else did she say?

39:02.818 --> 39:05.255
[wind howling]

39:05.299 --> 39:06.387
That's it.

39:12.741 --> 39:14.743
Why didn't you slow down, Karl?

39:14.787 --> 39:17.398
I could have been killed.
- Nina...

39:17.442 --> 39:19.182
You said that you could ride.

39:19.226 --> 39:21.097
How was I supposed to know
that saddle would come loose?

39:21.141 --> 39:24.623
I secured it myself.
It's a perfectly fine saddle.

39:24.666 --> 39:26.886
What the hell do you
want me to say?

39:29.976 --> 39:31.586
[distant knocking]

39:31.630 --> 39:34.241
[crickets chirping]

39:34.284 --> 39:37.679
Mr. Frederick,
terribly sorry to bother you
so late at night.

39:37.723 --> 39:39.986
We had a terrible accident
on Windham Road,

39:40.029 --> 39:42.075
and, unfortunately,
the driver was killed,

39:42.118 --> 39:45.426
and we think he may have been
coming from one of the homes
up here.

39:45.470 --> 39:47.428
So, I wanted to stop and check

39:47.472 --> 39:50.388
to see if you know
the name Yuri Vokhov.

39:50.431 --> 39:51.954
- Aw.
- Yuri?

39:52.868 --> 39:55.088
Yeah... Yeah, we...

39:55.131 --> 39:57.569
we-we-we do know him.
He's...

39:58.483 --> 40:00.049
My wife and I
recently got married.

40:00.093 --> 40:03.096
Yuri was her uncle, and he
was here recently, at a...

40:03.139 --> 40:06.708
little ceremony we had, and...

40:06.752 --> 40:09.276
As I recall,
he had too much to drink.

40:09.319 --> 40:11.844
Tried to get him to stay
the night, but he...

40:11.887 --> 40:14.107
he insisted on driving home.

40:15.064 --> 40:16.588
Oh.

40:16.631 --> 40:19.417
We're terribly sorry
for your loss.

40:19.460 --> 40:20.505
Thank you.

40:23.246 --> 40:25.945
[gentle piano music ♪]

40:25.988 --> 40:29.818
[wind howling]

40:39.915 --> 40:44.006
♪

41:07.552 --> 41:10.424
[dramatic musical sting ♪]

41:15.342 --> 41:18.954
[chilling music ♪]

41:20.434 --> 41:22.480
[Reign growls]

41:22.523 --> 41:24.482
[barking]

41:25.439 --> 41:28.007
[growling]

41:29.269 --> 41:31.793
[barks, whines]

41:42.195 --> 41:46.504
[eerie music ♪]

41:51.465 --> 41:54.555
[dramatic musical sting ♪]

41:54.599 --> 41:57.210
♪

42:08.613 --> 42:13.400
[crow cawing]

42:13.443 --> 42:16.446
[wind howling]

42:25.325 --> 42:29.459
♪

42:57.052 --> 42:58.488
I'm sorry.

42:58.532 --> 43:01.143
I didn't mean to
come in uninvited.

43:01.187 --> 43:03.493
[wind howling]

43:03.537 --> 43:04.930
I saw you working in the cold

43:04.973 --> 43:08.063
and thought you might
want something warm to eat.

43:08.107 --> 43:11.458
[chilling music ♪]

43:31.870 --> 43:34.873
So, I understand
you're from Hungary.

43:36.309 --> 43:40.705
I never been to Hungary,
but I hear it's very beautiful.

43:42.358 --> 43:45.274
I guess we are both
far from home.

43:51.846 --> 43:54.414
Karl says you like living here.

43:54.457 --> 43:55.981
We have so many bedrooms,

43:56.024 --> 43:57.373
why would you like
to sleep here...

43:57.417 --> 44:00.028
in the cold... alone... ?

44:05.730 --> 44:08.689
I want to believe that Karl
is a good man...

44:10.996 --> 44:13.694
but, between you and me,

44:13.738 --> 44:15.435
something is not right.

44:17.742 --> 44:19.700
Hagen...

44:19.744 --> 44:22.747
Did you write the warning for
me, on the kitchen window?

44:22.790 --> 44:24.226
"Run."

44:24.270 --> 44:25.750
Was that you?

44:25.793 --> 44:28.622
[chilling music ♪]

44:29.928 --> 44:31.669
It was you,
wasn't it?

44:33.061 --> 44:35.411
Are we in some kind of danger?

44:36.935 --> 44:38.719
[bowl clatters]

44:38.763 --> 44:40.678
Hagen, please!

44:44.638 --> 44:46.771
[weather vane creaking]

44:51.079 --> 44:53.734
[ominous music ♪]

45:15.451 --> 45:18.803
♪

45:47.701 --> 45:53.228
♪

46:04.892 --> 46:08.678
[generator humming]

46:08.722 --> 46:11.594
♪

46:30.483 --> 46:31.789
[clatter]

46:31.832 --> 46:33.703
[Maria speaking indistinctly]

46:33.747 --> 46:36.271
[clinking]

46:36.315 --> 46:37.969
Maria?

46:39.709 --> 46:41.320
Is everything okay?

46:42.321 --> 46:43.844
[Maria]
Everything is fine.

46:43.888 --> 46:46.281
♪

47:00.121 --> 47:03.385
[wind howling outside]

47:03.429 --> 47:05.866
I want to talk to Grandma.

47:05.910 --> 47:08.086
We talked with her yesterday.

47:08.738 --> 47:10.349
You talked to her yesterday

47:10.392 --> 47:11.916
about Uncle Yuri.

47:11.959 --> 47:13.743
You never let me talk.

47:17.182 --> 47:19.837
Okay. Maybe she's still awake.

47:25.451 --> 47:27.366
[phone playing jingling tune]

47:27.409 --> 47:28.193
[automated voice on phone]
This phone
has been disconnected

47:28.236 --> 47:29.455
due to non-payment.

47:29.498 --> 47:30.673
Please contact
Bell One Cellular

47:30.717 --> 47:31.413
to pay the past-due amount--

47:31.457 --> 47:32.371
What's the matter?

47:32.414 --> 47:32.980
I'll be back.

47:33.024 --> 47:34.721
You stay here.

47:34.764 --> 47:37.115
Don't go anywhere.

47:37.158 --> 47:39.769
[eerie music ♪]

47:49.083 --> 47:51.085
Is Maria okay?

47:51.129 --> 47:52.391
Yeah.

47:53.044 --> 47:55.524
Uh, I mean, no.
No, she's-

47:55.568 --> 47:56.743
she's not feeling well.

47:56.786 --> 48:00.138
She's-she's been up
all night vomiting.

48:00.181 --> 48:02.357
Oh, I hope she feels better.

48:03.663 --> 48:06.231
Nina, is there something
you wanted to ask me?

48:06.274 --> 48:07.362
Yes.

48:07.406 --> 48:08.886
My phone is not working.

48:08.929 --> 48:11.323
Dasha and I wanted
to call my mother.

48:11.366 --> 48:13.194
Didn't you call her yesterday?

48:13.238 --> 48:14.456
Yes, I did.

48:14.500 --> 48:16.415
And the day before.

48:16.458 --> 48:19.113
Maybe it's the connection, Nina.

48:19.157 --> 48:23.335
The message says its...
disconnected.

48:23.378 --> 48:25.903
♪

48:26.599 --> 48:27.861
[gasps]

48:31.647 --> 48:33.780
I guess I'll have to
call the phone company.

48:33.823 --> 48:36.391
[wind blowing outside]

48:37.697 --> 48:39.829
Well, how 'bout the house phone?

48:39.873 --> 48:43.094
They're obsolete,
at least in America.

48:44.704 --> 48:46.793
For such a big house
and so far from everything,

48:46.836 --> 48:48.708
what if there is
an emergency?

48:48.751 --> 48:50.536
Here. There's only one.

48:50.579 --> 48:51.972
International calls
are expensive,

48:52.016 --> 48:53.582
so make it quick.

48:53.626 --> 48:54.670
Hmm?

48:54.714 --> 48:55.802
It's okay.

48:55.845 --> 48:57.456
I'll call my mom later.

49:00.415 --> 49:01.677
Nina...

49:02.852 --> 49:04.289
I-I'm...

49:04.898 --> 49:06.073
I'm sorry.

49:07.205 --> 49:08.684
I know you've been
chomping at the bit

49:08.728 --> 49:10.817
to make yourself useful
around here, and...

49:10.860 --> 49:13.254
since Maria's
under the weather...

49:14.690 --> 49:17.737
how 'bout you make that Russian
meal we've been talkin' about?

49:18.999 --> 49:20.392
Just you and me?

49:21.045 --> 49:22.698
Maybe a little candlelight?

49:24.222 --> 49:25.919
Sure.

49:25.963 --> 49:27.181
Why not?

49:27.225 --> 49:30.532
[wind howling outside]

49:37.800 --> 49:41.935
[ambient music ♪]

49:41.979 --> 49:44.982
[crow cawing outside]

49:49.421 --> 49:51.249
[speaks Russian]

49:52.250 --> 49:53.642
Maria is not feeling well,

49:53.686 --> 49:56.950
so Karl asked me to make him
Russian dinner tonight.

49:56.994 --> 49:58.560
For just the two of us.

49:59.909 --> 50:03.652
You're a big girl.
You can entertain yourself,
right?

50:03.696 --> 50:05.915
Maybe you can eat dinner
in the playroom

50:05.959 --> 50:07.439
and watch a movie.

50:07.482 --> 50:09.702
[ominous music ♪]

50:09.745 --> 50:11.182
What's the matter?

50:13.575 --> 50:14.707
What's wrong?

50:17.231 --> 50:20.800
He-he came into my room
last night.

50:22.976 --> 50:24.673
What did he do?

50:24.717 --> 50:26.632
He sat next to me...

50:28.547 --> 50:30.679
...and he touched me.

50:30.723 --> 50:31.985
Touch you?

50:32.986 --> 50:33.943
How?

50:33.987 --> 50:35.858
[gentle music ♪]

50:35.902 --> 50:37.947
Like how you pet a dog.

50:37.991 --> 50:40.124
[dramatic music ♪]

50:41.603 --> 50:44.128
Well, I'm sure he
was just checking

50:44.171 --> 50:45.781
that you were feeling better.

50:50.177 --> 50:52.005
Dasha...

50:52.397 --> 50:54.442
[speaking Russian]

50:58.533 --> 50:59.969
Okay.

51:04.496 --> 51:07.151
[birds calling]

51:16.029 --> 51:18.118
[dramatic musical sting ♪]

51:18.162 --> 51:20.642
[chilling music ♪]

51:27.040 --> 51:29.303
All you ever do is work.

51:29.347 --> 51:31.349
Don't you do anything for fun?

51:31.392 --> 51:33.829
[chilling music ♪]

51:33.873 --> 51:34.961
Do you want to pull me?

51:35.004 --> 51:37.355
♪

51:44.405 --> 51:46.668
My mama's having dinner
with Karl,

51:46.712 --> 51:48.235
so I have to stay busy.

51:49.323 --> 51:51.456
I don't want to eat
with him anyway.

51:51.499 --> 51:53.719
[wind howling]

51:55.199 --> 51:57.026
You're good at this.

52:00.029 --> 52:01.379
The boy...

52:01.422 --> 52:02.510
who lived here...

52:02.554 --> 52:04.512
Were you friends with him?

52:12.129 --> 52:13.521
I knew it.

52:13.565 --> 52:16.698
I girl would go crazy
around here with no friends.

52:19.179 --> 52:21.442
What did you used to do
for fun?

52:30.103 --> 52:31.931
Wow!

52:33.976 --> 52:36.022
He like movies.

52:36.065 --> 52:38.111
I like movies.

52:38.155 --> 52:40.809
I like vampire movies,

52:40.853 --> 52:43.072
monster movies,

52:43.116 --> 52:45.684
space movies,

52:45.727 --> 52:47.686
all kinds of movies.

52:49.253 --> 52:50.428
What's your favorite?

52:57.130 --> 52:59.001
[delicate instrumental music ♪]

53:07.401 --> 53:10.404
Well, you've really outdone
yourself, haven't you, Nina?

53:10.448 --> 53:13.712
It's roasted apples,
potatoes and duck,

53:13.755 --> 53:16.062
one of Dasha's favorites.

53:16.105 --> 53:18.717
Oh, well,
if it's Dasha's favorite,

53:18.760 --> 53:20.240
it must be good.

53:24.244 --> 53:26.942
Mmh, mmh, mmh.

53:27.334 --> 53:29.380
That is something.

53:29.423 --> 53:31.425
[electricity humming]

53:31.469 --> 53:32.905
Ugh.

53:32.948 --> 53:35.908
Damned power outages are
happening way too frequently.

53:35.951 --> 53:37.126
Yes.

53:37.170 --> 53:40.304
Last night, the generator
woke me up.

53:40.347 --> 53:42.697
You were not in bed.
- Hmm.

53:42.741 --> 53:45.961
I was down in the cellar
refueling the generator.

53:50.314 --> 53:53.273
Dasha says that you
were in here room.

53:58.974 --> 54:00.585
Are you accusing me
of something?

54:00.628 --> 54:03.457
I just want to know
why you were in here room.

54:03.501 --> 54:05.372
♪

54:05.416 --> 54:07.331
She also says that...

54:08.941 --> 54:10.116
...you touched her.

54:10.159 --> 54:12.640
[fire crackling]

54:12.684 --> 54:15.382
I was checking to see
if she had a fever.

54:15.426 --> 54:17.645
In case you forgot,
she almost drowned.

54:20.300 --> 54:22.041
What else is bothering you,
Nina?

54:23.260 --> 54:25.958
I know you haven't been happy,

54:26.001 --> 54:27.786
so let's just get it out.

54:32.094 --> 54:35.402
[girl on movie]
You have those,
and I'll have these.

54:35.446 --> 54:38.318
[projector clicking]

54:39.928 --> 54:42.279
I can make a boat.

54:42.322 --> 54:45.673
[ominous music ♪]

54:46.370 --> 54:48.285
See how mine floats?

54:53.377 --> 54:55.074
No, you're hurting me!

54:55.117 --> 54:56.423
No!

55:03.909 --> 55:06.128
♪

55:06.172 --> 55:08.217
You never wanted a wife.

55:08.261 --> 55:09.567
Did you?

55:11.003 --> 55:12.265
No.

55:14.093 --> 55:17.009
But, I have to admit,
you made a believer
out of me.

55:17.052 --> 55:18.880
I mean,
you're an amazing cook,

55:18.924 --> 55:20.012
devoted wife,

55:20.055 --> 55:22.188
a wonderful mother,

55:22.231 --> 55:24.321
and you give a mean blowjob.

55:25.060 --> 55:26.845
The truth is, Nina,

55:26.888 --> 55:30.022
you've made this very difficult
for me.

55:31.415 --> 55:34.374
I don't understand what you're
talking about.

55:34.418 --> 55:35.810
No.

55:35.854 --> 55:37.334
Of course, you don't.

55:38.378 --> 55:39.379
Why would you?

55:44.558 --> 55:46.212
I was watching a show,
the other night,

55:46.255 --> 55:47.996
about the Donner Party.

55:48.040 --> 55:50.303
You ever heard
of the Donner Party?

55:51.348 --> 55:52.436
No.

55:54.133 --> 55:56.657
1846, 87 American settlers

55:56.701 --> 55:58.398
got trapped
in the Sierra Mountains,

55:58.442 --> 56:00.444
in a blizzard, snowstorm.

56:00.487 --> 56:02.228
Temperatures dropped
below freezing,

56:02.271 --> 56:04.273
food supplies ran dry.

56:04.317 --> 56:09.148
Of the 87, 48 actually survived.

56:09.888 --> 56:11.368
Do you know why?

56:14.458 --> 56:16.024
They ate the dead.

56:17.156 --> 56:18.766
Their loved ones.

56:20.377 --> 56:21.595
So, it got me to thinking

56:21.639 --> 56:24.642
about you and me and Dasha...

56:24.685 --> 56:26.731
If it was just the three of us
trapped alone

56:26.774 --> 56:29.168
in this big house,
without food,

56:29.211 --> 56:30.648
getting hungrier and hungrier...

56:30.691 --> 56:32.345
What does this has to
do with anything...

56:32.389 --> 56:33.607
...for Dasha's sake.

56:33.651 --> 56:35.043
It was a big mistake for us
to come here.

56:35.087 --> 56:37.350
Would you kill me?

56:38.786 --> 56:40.658
And eat me?

56:41.485 --> 56:42.399
What?

56:42.442 --> 56:45.314
Would you kill me
and eat me

56:45.358 --> 56:46.446
for Dasha's sake?

56:46.490 --> 56:48.361
Would you take a knife,

56:48.405 --> 56:51.320
carve me up...

56:51.364 --> 56:53.279
and eat me?

56:53.322 --> 56:55.324
You really are crazy,
aren't you?

56:55.368 --> 56:57.283
It's really
a pretty simple question.

56:57.326 --> 56:58.632
I just wanna know

56:58.676 --> 57:00.460
if we see eyes to eye.

57:00.504 --> 57:02.375
[ominous music ♪]

57:02.419 --> 57:04.203
No, Karl.

57:04.246 --> 57:05.552
We don't.

57:06.292 --> 57:09.600
[projector clicking]

57:09.643 --> 57:16.650
[dramatic music on film ♪]

57:16.694 --> 57:19.392
[chilling music ♪]

57:26.486 --> 57:27.487
Well?

57:28.706 --> 57:30.359
It's been really swell.

57:32.710 --> 57:35.408
I don't know about you,
but I'm ready for dessert.

57:35.452 --> 57:37.149
There is no dessert.

57:37.192 --> 57:38.542
No worries.

57:38.585 --> 57:42.850
Maria made an amazing
apple pie, just yesterday.

57:42.894 --> 57:44.504
Do you like it
a la mode?

57:44.548 --> 57:46.332
I'm sorry, Karl.

57:46.375 --> 57:48.247
Tomorrow, I'm taking Dasha,

57:48.290 --> 57:50.379
and we are leaving.

57:50.423 --> 57:54.514
[Karl roars]
[dramatic musical sting ♪]

57:56.647 --> 57:59.345
[dramatic, ambient music ♪]

58:16.623 --> 58:19.583
[dramatic musical sting ♪]

58:19.626 --> 58:22.716
Mr. Fredrick, you did
the right thing.

58:25.284 --> 58:28.417
I should have told her
the truth.

58:28.461 --> 58:31.856
The truth would not have
made any difference.

58:31.899 --> 58:34.249
You are blinded by her beauty.

58:34.293 --> 58:35.642
[ominous music ♪]

58:35.686 --> 58:38.297
But I can see the wolf
in sheep's clothing.

58:49.047 --> 58:52.485
[shuddering breaths]

59:06.543 --> 59:07.805
Karl!

59:09.937 --> 59:10.808
[pounding]

59:10.851 --> 59:13.593
Let me out!

59:13.637 --> 59:16.204
Karl, I'm freezing!

59:22.123 --> 59:26.563
Karl!

59:30.262 --> 59:32.090
[wind howling]

59:40.707 --> 59:42.448
[Dasha]
Karl.

59:42.491 --> 59:45.625
[unsettling, ambient music ♪]

59:45.669 --> 59:48.193
Please let my mom go.

59:52.501 --> 59:53.590
Please?

59:58.072 --> 1:00:01.119
Please let my mom go.

1:00:01.162 --> 1:00:03.077
I beg you, please.

1:00:04.122 --> 1:00:05.906
I will do anything.

1:00:05.950 --> 1:00:07.560
Anything.

1:00:08.605 --> 1:00:09.693
Please.

1:00:10.607 --> 1:00:11.869
[smack]

1:00:11.912 --> 1:00:13.697
[crying]
Please.

1:00:13.740 --> 1:00:15.307
[grunts]
Please.

1:00:15.350 --> 1:00:17.048
Don't hurt my mom.

1:00:17.091 --> 1:00:18.527
Please.

1:00:18.571 --> 1:00:19.659
What is going on here?

1:00:19.703 --> 1:00:22.357
I beg you.
I beg you.

1:00:22.401 --> 1:00:23.663
[Maria]
That's enough!

1:00:23.707 --> 1:00:25.317
No more games!

1:00:25.360 --> 1:00:27.624
It's time for you
to join Tyler.
- No!

1:00:27.667 --> 1:00:29.669
I hate you!
You're a monster!

1:00:29.713 --> 1:00:31.976
I hate you!
[crying]

1:00:32.019 --> 1:00:33.368
[Maria]
Come this way!

1:00:36.633 --> 1:00:39.548
[panting]

1:00:39.592 --> 1:00:41.072
[grunts]

1:00:41.115 --> 1:00:43.770
[eerie ambience]

1:01:04.443 --> 1:01:06.663
Son of a bitch.

1:01:24.768 --> 1:01:28.989
[fire crackling]

1:01:29.033 --> 1:01:33.559
[crowd on video]
♪ Happy birthday to you

1:01:33.602 --> 1:01:37.955
♪ Happy birthday to you

1:01:37.998 --> 1:01:43.090
♪ Happy birthday,
dear Tyler ♪

1:01:43.134 --> 1:01:47.704
♪ Happy birthday to you

1:01:47.747 --> 1:01:50.663
[crowd on video applauding]

1:01:50.707 --> 1:01:53.753
[ominous music ♪]

1:02:10.596 --> 1:02:12.424
A puppy!

1:02:12.467 --> 1:02:15.819
[crowd on video laughing,
chattering]

1:02:15.862 --> 1:02:17.646
I love you, Daddy.

1:02:20.693 --> 1:02:22.434
I love you, Son.

1:02:25.176 --> 1:02:27.613
[power goes out with a boom]

1:02:29.789 --> 1:02:32.096
[electricity buzzing]

1:02:32.139 --> 1:02:34.794
[ominous music ♪]

1:02:50.723 --> 1:02:54.727
[generator pounding]

1:03:15.313 --> 1:03:17.794
[indiscernible murmuring]

1:03:25.758 --> 1:03:28.108
[chilling music ♪]

1:03:28.152 --> 1:03:31.764
[rumbling]

1:03:38.292 --> 1:03:39.772
You.

1:03:40.381 --> 1:03:42.775
Do you see what you've done?

1:03:42.819 --> 1:03:45.038
[dramatic musical sting ♪]

1:03:45.082 --> 1:03:47.824
♪

1:04:04.014 --> 1:04:07.713
♪

1:04:09.802 --> 1:04:14.633
[grunting]

1:04:25.862 --> 1:04:29.953
[dramatic music ♪]

1:04:29.996 --> 1:04:31.737
[crowbar clangs]

1:04:43.967 --> 1:04:45.664
[grunts]

1:04:56.544 --> 1:04:58.416
[gasps]

1:05:14.954 --> 1:05:19.437
♪

1:05:34.843 --> 1:05:38.412
[grunting]

1:05:57.127 --> 1:05:59.912
[grunting]

1:06:05.526 --> 1:06:08.921
[generator rumbling]

1:06:21.020 --> 1:06:22.630
[panting]

1:06:22.674 --> 1:06:24.241
It's nice to see you, too.

1:06:36.688 --> 1:06:39.038
[fire crackling]

1:06:39.082 --> 1:06:41.954
[eerie music ♪]

1:06:44.522 --> 1:06:46.176
Wake up.

1:06:48.004 --> 1:06:51.007
If you touched a hair
on her head

1:06:51.050 --> 1:06:52.747
I'll kill you.

1:06:54.184 --> 1:06:56.273
Even know how to use it?

1:06:56.316 --> 1:06:59.363
My father taught me many things.

1:07:00.407 --> 1:07:02.279
Take me to her.

1:07:02.322 --> 1:07:04.933
Oh, what are you gonna do,
Nina?

1:07:06.935 --> 1:07:09.503
I'm a respected man,

1:07:09.547 --> 1:07:11.288
and you're what...

1:07:11.331 --> 1:07:13.203
exactly?

1:07:13.246 --> 1:07:15.074
Ordered by mail...

1:07:16.989 --> 1:07:18.773
Delivered...

1:07:19.948 --> 1:07:22.603
You think the police
are gonna believe you?

1:07:23.822 --> 1:07:24.910
[Nina]
No.

1:07:24.953 --> 1:07:27.434
But maybe they will
believe Lucia.

1:07:30.133 --> 1:07:31.525
You talked to Lucia?

1:07:31.569 --> 1:07:33.788
I found her in the cellar.

1:07:33.832 --> 1:07:35.529
Oh.

1:07:35.573 --> 1:07:37.053
Right.

1:07:37.096 --> 1:07:39.620
[dramatic music ♪]

1:07:41.535 --> 1:07:43.711
That was an accident.

1:07:43.755 --> 1:07:45.104
Like the saddle?

1:07:45.148 --> 1:07:47.933
Let's just cut the crap,
huh?

1:07:47.976 --> 1:07:50.544
You want the truth?

1:07:50.588 --> 1:07:52.720
She had it coming.

1:07:52.764 --> 1:07:55.984
She carried the disease
in her family.
She never told me.

1:07:56.028 --> 1:07:57.160
You think
I would've married her,

1:07:57.203 --> 1:07:58.944
let alone
let her bear my child?!

1:07:58.987 --> 1:08:01.990
For Christ's sake, he was dying
the moment he was born!

1:08:02.034 --> 1:08:03.296
I'm sorry,

1:08:03.340 --> 1:08:05.255
but that has nothing to do
with my daughter.

1:08:05.298 --> 1:08:08.519
I-I'm tired
of this song and dance, really.

1:08:08.562 --> 1:08:10.129
Wooh!
[chuckles]

1:08:10.173 --> 1:08:12.566
Why don't you just
do us both a favor, huh?

1:08:12.610 --> 1:08:16.875
You summon the courage, and you
pull the fucking trigger.

1:08:18.181 --> 1:08:19.660
Do it.

1:08:22.359 --> 1:08:24.230
Do it!

1:08:24.274 --> 1:08:26.014
[gasping]

1:08:26.058 --> 1:08:28.147
Do it!

1:08:28.191 --> 1:08:30.323
[Nina crying out]

1:08:30.367 --> 1:08:32.151
[crying]

1:08:32.195 --> 1:08:35.198
Please, Karl,
just give her to me.

1:08:35.241 --> 1:08:37.025
[dramatic music ♪]

1:08:39.115 --> 1:08:40.725
Please, Karl.

1:08:41.900 --> 1:08:43.031
Please.

1:08:43.075 --> 1:08:44.903
I'm sorry, Nina,

1:08:44.946 --> 1:08:46.774
but I can't let you go.

1:08:46.818 --> 1:08:49.081
♪

1:08:49.125 --> 1:08:51.562
Therein lies
one simple question.

1:08:51.605 --> 1:08:53.868
[gentle music ♪]

1:08:53.912 --> 1:08:56.784
Is there any way we can
make this marriage work?

1:08:59.613 --> 1:09:00.832
Go to hell.

1:09:00.875 --> 1:09:02.703
I want my daughter!

1:09:02.747 --> 1:09:04.444
[panting]

1:09:05.097 --> 1:09:07.186
[shotgun blast]

1:09:07.230 --> 1:09:09.928
[dramatic music ♪]

1:09:09.971 --> 1:09:12.626
[gasping]

1:09:19.981 --> 1:09:20.721
No!

1:09:21.157 --> 1:09:23.115
No!

1:09:24.595 --> 1:09:26.510
I'm very sorry...

1:09:27.685 --> 1:09:30.209
...it's come down
to this, Nina.

1:09:30.253 --> 1:09:31.906
[Nina, crying]
No!

1:09:31.950 --> 1:09:33.821
No, please!

1:09:33.865 --> 1:09:35.823
I'm begging you, no!

1:09:35.867 --> 1:09:41.046
[screaming]
No!

1:09:41.089 --> 1:09:45.703
[ominous ambience]

1:09:45.746 --> 1:09:49.097
[distorted noise]

1:09:54.320 --> 1:09:56.104
[Nina]
Dasha...

1:09:57.671 --> 1:09:59.934
I want to see Dasha.

1:10:02.198 --> 1:10:03.199
[gasps]

1:10:11.903 --> 1:10:14.210
[knocks on door]

1:10:17.822 --> 1:10:21.129
[unsettling music ♪]

1:10:31.183 --> 1:10:35.187
You'll be happy to know
I managed to save both thumbs,
and an index finger.

1:10:37.320 --> 1:10:39.278
You don't feel any pain
because I've had you

1:10:39.322 --> 1:10:41.106
on a steady drip
of diamorphine

1:10:41.149 --> 1:10:42.847
for several weeks now.

1:10:43.891 --> 1:10:45.502
The snow has melted.

1:10:46.372 --> 1:10:48.331
Spring is in the air.

1:10:49.593 --> 1:10:50.985
A new day.

1:10:52.117 --> 1:10:53.292
Where is Dasha?

1:10:53.336 --> 1:10:55.294
Oh, Dasha...
[shushing]

1:10:55.338 --> 1:10:57.209
She's fine.

1:10:57.253 --> 1:10:58.471
She's resting.

1:11:00.473 --> 1:11:03.171
I respect you, Nina.

1:11:03.215 --> 1:11:04.303
As a woman.

1:11:05.478 --> 1:11:06.827
And a mother.

1:11:08.220 --> 1:11:12.311
I could've easily blown
your head off, but...

1:11:12.355 --> 1:11:13.573
...the truth is...

1:11:14.357 --> 1:11:16.097
...something stopped me.

1:11:17.882 --> 1:11:19.318
My father used to always say,

1:11:19.362 --> 1:11:21.407
"Any woman
who can survive a month

1:11:21.451 --> 1:11:23.148
with a Fredrick

1:11:23.191 --> 1:11:25.063
is a keeper."

1:11:25.106 --> 1:11:26.804
Hmm-hmm.

1:11:31.374 --> 1:11:35.247
My mother lasted four years
before she tried
to steal me away.

1:11:39.207 --> 1:11:40.992
The memories of that night...

1:11:42.167 --> 1:11:43.777
...seared into my brain.

1:11:46.258 --> 1:11:48.304
The unspeakable acts
he did to her.

1:11:52.220 --> 1:11:55.180
Afterward, he pulled me aside.
He said, "Karl...

1:11:55.223 --> 1:11:58.270
there's nothing more sacred
to a man than his son.

1:11:59.445 --> 1:12:01.055
Nothing."

1:12:02.535 --> 1:12:04.581
But you taught me something,
Nina.

1:12:10.413 --> 1:12:12.240
A mother's love also matters.

1:12:16.723 --> 1:12:19.596
That's why I've decided
to spare you.

1:12:19.639 --> 1:12:21.685
I want to give you a chance.

1:12:22.860 --> 1:12:25.732
A chance that Lucia
and my mother never had.

1:12:27.125 --> 1:12:28.822
Do you want that chance, Nina?

1:12:28.866 --> 1:12:31.085
[moans softly]

1:12:32.957 --> 1:12:34.393
Good.

1:12:35.438 --> 1:12:36.700
Good.

1:12:38.354 --> 1:12:40.356
Now, let's take a little stroll.
Shall we?

1:12:42.836 --> 1:12:46.492
[ominous music ♪]

1:13:03.509 --> 1:13:05.337
Dasha?

1:13:07.470 --> 1:13:09.341
[Karl]
Dasha's fine.

1:13:09.385 --> 1:13:10.690
She's just sleeping.

1:13:10.734 --> 1:13:13.301
[heart monitor beeping]

1:13:13.345 --> 1:13:14.346
Maria,

1:13:14.390 --> 1:13:16.304
could you give us
a moment alone?

1:13:16.348 --> 1:13:20.178
Why is she...

1:13:20.221 --> 1:13:22.702
Because this is why she's here.

1:13:22.746 --> 1:13:25.357
To make a difference for you...

1:13:26.314 --> 1:13:28.012
...for me...

1:13:30.362 --> 1:13:32.277
...for my son.

1:13:32.320 --> 1:13:34.975
[dramatic musical sting ♪]

1:13:44.420 --> 1:13:47.771
Say hello to Tyler.

1:13:47.814 --> 1:13:49.686
He's beautiful, isn't he?

1:13:52.732 --> 1:13:54.342
Just a boy

1:13:54.386 --> 1:13:56.910
who wants nothing more

1:13:56.954 --> 1:13:58.303
than to grow up,

1:13:58.346 --> 1:13:59.739
go to school...

1:14:01.480 --> 1:14:02.742
...play ball...

1:14:03.961 --> 1:14:05.745
...have that first kiss...

1:14:05.789 --> 1:14:07.878
[dramatic music ♪]

1:14:07.921 --> 1:14:11.142
Tyler needs
a stem cell transplant.

1:14:11.185 --> 1:14:13.405
He also needs lungs...

1:14:14.188 --> 1:14:15.363
...and a heart.

1:14:15.407 --> 1:14:19.411
♪

1:14:26.549 --> 1:14:29.160
I, uh...
I put him on a donors list.

1:14:29.203 --> 1:14:30.988
I offered to pay
the board millions,

1:14:31.031 --> 1:14:32.772
but they said
that his chance of survival

1:14:32.816 --> 1:14:34.513
was too low.

1:14:34.557 --> 1:14:36.689
I could've gotten the organs
in Mexico on the black market,

1:14:36.733 --> 1:14:38.125
but you...

1:14:38.169 --> 1:14:40.258
you never know
what you're getting.

1:14:40.301 --> 1:14:41.520
So, my Russian colleagues

1:14:41.564 --> 1:14:43.479
tested hundred of children

1:14:43.522 --> 1:14:45.350
to find the perfect match.

1:14:45.393 --> 1:14:48.875
A young, healthy donor.

1:14:51.312 --> 1:14:52.488
Nina...

1:14:54.446 --> 1:14:57.014
He's my flesh and blood.

1:14:57.057 --> 1:14:58.276
I had to do this.

1:14:58.319 --> 1:15:00.234
- Please--
- Shh, shh, shh.

1:15:00.278 --> 1:15:02.759
They say, "Mother is God

1:15:02.802 --> 1:15:04.412
on the lips of children."

1:15:05.588 --> 1:15:09.026
Tyler's going to need a mother.
I'm not going to live forever.

1:15:10.418 --> 1:15:14.161
The marriage papers we signed
are very real.

1:15:14.205 --> 1:15:17.556
Everything I have is yours
after I'm gone.

1:15:20.603 --> 1:15:22.605
Look on the bright side.

1:15:22.648 --> 1:15:25.564
Dasha will always be here...

1:15:25.608 --> 1:15:27.218
living in Tyler.

1:15:28.524 --> 1:15:30.656
[dramatic music ♪]

1:15:35.661 --> 1:15:37.489
The others will be here soon.

1:15:37.533 --> 1:15:39.404
We should prepare for surgery.

1:15:39.447 --> 1:15:40.797
Yes. Yes, of course.

1:15:40.840 --> 1:15:43.626
Please just take her back
and increase her dosage.

1:15:43.669 --> 1:15:46.585
I want her heavily sedated
during surgery.

1:15:46.629 --> 1:15:48.108
Oh, and put Reign away.

1:15:48.152 --> 1:15:51.503
I don't want him
bothering our guests.

1:15:51.547 --> 1:15:53.418
[sighs deeply]

1:15:55.638 --> 1:15:57.814
[dramatic music ♪]

1:15:59.946 --> 1:16:02.688
- Please...
- Oh, please, please, Maria...

1:16:02.732 --> 1:16:04.211
Are you kidding me?

1:16:04.255 --> 1:16:07.475
If I had my way,
you would've been dead
a long time ago.

1:16:07.519 --> 1:16:10.261
I am the one who has
been loyal to him!

1:16:10.304 --> 1:16:11.871
Fed him, clothed him.

1:16:11.915 --> 1:16:13.873
One day,
this will all be mine!

1:16:13.917 --> 1:16:15.745
And I will be more
of a mother to Tyler

1:16:15.788 --> 1:16:17.703
than you could ever be!

1:16:19.487 --> 1:16:21.098
[Nina groaning]

1:16:24.667 --> 1:16:26.146
Sleep tight...

1:16:26.190 --> 1:16:27.670
forever.

1:16:27.713 --> 1:16:30.368
[footsteps leaving]

1:16:31.369 --> 1:16:32.849
[door slams]

1:16:45.688 --> 1:16:48.560
[gasping]

1:16:49.213 --> 1:16:51.476
[dramatic musical sting ♪]

1:16:58.614 --> 1:17:02.574
[ominous music ♪]

1:17:03.575 --> 1:17:05.490
[Nina]
No, oh....

1:17:05.533 --> 1:17:07.535
[grunting]

1:17:08.711 --> 1:17:10.364
Dasha!

1:17:11.714 --> 1:17:13.324
Dasha!

1:17:13.367 --> 1:17:16.153
♪

1:17:17.720 --> 1:17:20.548
[gasping]

1:17:28.034 --> 1:17:31.168
[heart monitor beeping]

1:17:31.211 --> 1:17:35.738
♪

1:17:39.698 --> 1:17:44.660
[dramatic, operatic music ♪]

1:17:53.581 --> 1:17:56.149
[engine starts]

1:18:00.545 --> 1:18:02.590
Mom... Mama!

1:18:02.634 --> 1:18:04.549
We can't leave without my mom!

1:18:04.592 --> 1:18:06.638
Stop the car!
Stop the--

1:18:09.685 --> 1:18:11.338
[grunts]

1:18:11.382 --> 1:18:13.732
♪

1:18:13.776 --> 1:18:16.430
[grunting]

1:18:20.043 --> 1:18:20.913
No!

1:18:20.957 --> 1:18:23.133
[Hagen grunting]

1:18:23.176 --> 1:18:24.569
[growls]

1:18:24.612 --> 1:18:26.440
After everything my family's
done for you...

1:18:26.484 --> 1:18:28.138
this is how you repay us?

1:18:28.181 --> 1:18:29.792
Huh?

1:18:29.835 --> 1:18:32.185
He's not a very nice man,
Dasha.

1:18:32.229 --> 1:18:33.665
After the wedding,

1:18:33.709 --> 1:18:35.841
he murdered your Uncle Yuri.

1:18:36.929 --> 1:18:38.714
That's right.

1:18:38.757 --> 1:18:41.194
He ran your uncle's car
off the road,

1:18:41.238 --> 1:18:44.589
