on fire with gasoline.

1:18:45.808 --> 1:18:47.635
Not a nice thing to do.

1:18:47.679 --> 1:18:48.985
[gunshot]

1:18:51.727 --> 1:18:52.728
[gasps]

1:18:53.729 --> 1:18:56.296
[whimpering]

1:18:57.820 --> 1:18:59.735
At least, when I kill,

1:18:59.778 --> 1:19:01.214
it's for the greater good.

1:19:01.258 --> 1:19:02.781
You do it
'cause you're told

1:19:02.825 --> 1:19:04.783
like a fucking dog.

1:19:04.827 --> 1:19:07.177
You know what happens
when dogs misbehave?

1:19:07.220 --> 1:19:08.613
[gunshot]

1:19:08.656 --> 1:19:11.050
[screams]

1:19:11.094 --> 1:19:14.053
♪

1:19:18.231 --> 1:19:19.319
Take her!

1:19:23.149 --> 1:19:26.326
[wind howling]

1:19:26.370 --> 1:19:28.807
[dramatic music ♪]

1:19:28.851 --> 1:19:31.810
Welcome!
Welcome, welcome, welcome.

1:19:35.248 --> 1:19:39.252
♪

1:19:39.296 --> 1:19:40.993
Oh, don't mind him.

1:19:41.037 --> 1:19:43.517
He's just the groundskeeper.

1:19:44.736 --> 1:19:46.129
Darling.

1:19:46.172 --> 1:19:48.261
Just on time.

1:19:48.305 --> 1:19:51.830
Karl, this is Doctor Gorvinski,
transplant specialist,

1:19:51.874 --> 1:19:53.832
and the founder
of Russian Love-Line.

1:19:53.876 --> 1:19:55.312
Pleasure to meet you.

1:19:55.355 --> 1:19:57.836
[Russian accent]
So sorry for the delays.

1:19:57.880 --> 1:19:59.751
It's first time I ever
have problem

1:19:59.795 --> 1:20:01.231
with visa.

1:20:01.274 --> 1:20:03.842
It's like there is resurgence
of Cold War tensions.

1:20:03.886 --> 1:20:05.713
Yes, yes, terrible,
terrible, terrible.

1:20:05.757 --> 1:20:07.019
Let's go inside.
It's beginning to rain.

1:20:07.063 --> 1:20:08.151
Shall we?
- Yes.

1:20:08.194 --> 1:20:09.848
Come, come.
- Everyone?

1:20:09.892 --> 1:20:11.284
Keller.

1:20:12.372 --> 1:20:15.245
Make me proud.

1:20:15.288 --> 1:20:17.334
All right?
Go on.

1:20:17.377 --> 1:20:18.726
[sighs]

1:20:23.731 --> 1:20:25.864
[wind howling]

1:20:25.908 --> 1:20:26.996
[gunshot]

1:20:30.347 --> 1:20:33.654
[ominous music ♪]

1:20:35.787 --> 1:20:38.529
[thunder crashes]

1:20:38.572 --> 1:20:40.705
[rain pouring]

1:20:42.446 --> 1:20:46.102
[heart monitor beeping]

1:20:56.068 --> 1:20:58.027
[thunder]

1:21:00.246 --> 1:21:02.509
[elevator clattering]

1:21:02.553 --> 1:21:05.556
♪

1:21:13.564 --> 1:21:16.001
[saw buzzes]

1:21:25.706 --> 1:21:27.708
[saw buzzing]

1:21:28.840 --> 1:21:31.147
[clattering loudly]

1:21:41.244 --> 1:21:44.638
